# Text encoding policy

This repository’s text files are **UTF-8 without BOM**, with **LF** line endings.

## Default assumption (do this)

- Open and edit all source/docs as UTF-8 (no BOM). Do **not** guess CP949 / EUC-KR / UTF-16.
- Do **not** start tasks with “먼저 UTF-8로 변환하겠습니다” or bulk re-encoding.
- New and modified files must be saved as UTF-8 (no BOM), LF.
- Project defaults: `.editorconfig`, `.vscode/settings.json` (`files.encoding: utf8`, `files.eol: \n`, `files.autoGuessEncoding: false`), `.gitattributes` (`eol=lf`).

## When conversion is allowed (exception only)

Convert a file **only if** you have concrete evidence it is not UTF-8 no-BOM, for example:

- UTF-8 BOM (`EF BB BF`)
- UTF-16 BOM (`FF FE` / `FE FF`)
- Invalid UTF-8 byte sequences
- Mojibake that is clearly from wrong decoding of this repo’s Korean strings

Then convert **that file only** to UTF-8 (no BOM) + LF. Do not change code logic—encoding and line endings only. Verify Hangul is intact after conversion.

## Out of scope

- Binary assets (`png`, `jpg`, `webp`, `db`, fonts, etc.)
- Generated/cache dirs (`node_modules`, `.next`, `.next-dev`, `data/`)
